On September 27, 2020, Melania and Donald Trump released a statement wishing Jewish people around the world a blessed Yom Kippur. They acknowledged the significance of Yom Kippur as the end of the High Holy Days, a period of repentance, prayer, fasting, and fellowship. They also highlighted the importance of faith during the ongoing challenges posed by the coronavirus pandemic. The statement encouraged incorporating virtues of compassion into daily lives and wished all Jewish people an easy fast and a meaningful Yom Kippur.